<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-29 13:58 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0211 &Cx1f; ttj-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HN     12-29 0150
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-HEARST-NEWS-BUDGET-HNS </SLUG>
  
 Tuesday, Dec. 29, 1998    
 Editors      The Hearst News Service will file the following
stories for Wednesday. If you have questions, please call Susie
McBee or Tim Spence at 202-298-6920.    (The ``HNS'' tag appears in
all sluglines.)   
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON NEWS (``w'' category)
</P>
<P>
   OLYMPIC-INVESTIGATION (Washington) _ Former U.S. Sen. George
Mitchell, who heads the U.S. Olympics Committee's probe of
allegations that bribes helped Salt Lake City win the 2002 Winter
Olympic Games, promises a quick and thorough investigation. By MARK
HELM.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ As we enter the final year of this
century, we can wrap up an astounding 100 years either with a
whimper or a bang. If 1899 is any guide, we won't do anything
special _ beyond settling President Clinton's fate, that is. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
