<P>
   WRGRACE-TOXIC (Woburn, Mass.) _ Until the early 1970s, W.R.
Grace dumped toxics into a ditch, never imagining they might reach
public water supplies. That carelessness cast W.R. Grace &AMP; Co. as a
villain in one of the most famous environmental trials in US
history. By Scott Allen. 1750 words. (a and f coding)
