<P>
   MURDOCH-BAYLEY _ (Oxford, England) _ Iris Murdoch, the
celebrated author of 26 rigorously intellectual novels, stood
uncertainly in the doorway of her living room, her face frozen in
the blank expression that is a sure badge of Alzheimer's disease.
It was only when she saw her husband, the critic, professor and
novelist John Bayley, that a flicker of comprehension sparked in
her eyes. But it was gone, as quickly as it came. Bayley talks
about his 40 years Murdoch, and his new memoir, ``Elegy for Iris,''
due out in January. By Sarah Lyall.
</P>
<P>
   AFFLICTION-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Affliction'': Paul
Schrader, writer/director; with Nick Nolte, James Coburn, Sissy
Spacek, Willem Dafoe. Reviewed by Janet Maslin.
</P>
<P>
   HILARY-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``Hilary and Jackie'': Anand
Tucker, director; with Emily Watson, Rachel Griffiths. Reviewed by
Stephen Holden.
</P>
<P>
   COUNTRY-FILM-REVIEW (Undated) _ ``The Hi-Lo Country'': Stephen
Frears, director; with Billy Crudup, Woody Harrelson, Patricia
Arquette. Reviewed by Stephen Holden.
</P>
