<HEADLINE>
DIGGING INTO THE ORIGINS OF SPAM
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Why is junk E-mail called ``spam''?
</P>
<P>
   _ G.D., via the Internet
</P>
<P>
   A: Spam is used to describe several different means of flooding
the Internet with the same information, according to the Free
Online Dictionary of Computing.
</P>
<P>
   An E-mail that is sent to thousands of people at the same time
is commonly called a spam.
</P>
<P>
   The inspiration for the term is a ``Monty Python's Flying
Circus'' skit in which a restaurant works Spam luncheon meat into
most of its menu choices. Dishes include egg and Spam; bacon and
Spam; bacon, sausage and Spam; and ``lobster thermidor aux
crevettes with a mornay sauce garnished with truffle pate brandy
and a fried egg on top of Spam.''
</P>
<P>
   The Hormel Co. reportedly chose the name Spam by combining the
words ``spices'' and ``ham,'' according to the New York Public
Library Book of Popular Americana.
</P>
<P>
   Q: My daughter is a big fan of Charlize Theron from ``Devil's
Advocate'' and other movies. Where can I write to request an
autographed picture?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.P., Colleyville, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Theron in care of United Talent Agency, 9560
Wilshire Blvd., Suite 500, Beverly Hills, CA 90212.
</P>
<P>
   The 23-year-old model broke into acting with ``2 Days in the
Valley'' after losing out on the ``Showgirls'' lead role that went
to Elizabeth Berkley.
</P>
<P>
   Theron, a native South African who grew up on a rural farm, came
to the United States at age 18 and stayed to pursue modeling and
ballet. A knee injury ended her dance career in 1995.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I contact the makers of ONZE Mineral Skin Care? I'm
having trouble finding their product.
</P>
<P>
   _ J.D., Euless, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The ONZE company sells its products directly through mail
order. A catalog of its products is available by calling (800)
866-7151. The catalog's $2 cost is refunded upon an initial order.
</P>
<P>
   You also can order ONZE products from its Web site at
www.onzedirect.com.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
</TEXT>
