<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FOOD-NOTES-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FOOD NOTES: QUALITY SEAFOOD; CHOCOLATE AND FRIENDS; CUT-RATE
CATERING 
</HEADLINE>
  (lb) 
 By FLORENCE FABRICANT   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ A small display at 255 Elizabeth St. (Houston
Street), the new retail outlet of Wild Edibles, the seafood
wholesaler, only hints at how much seafood there is for sale. A
chalkboard inside the storefront lists all the other sea fare
sequestered in the chilly back room.
</P>
<P>
   Don't expect bargains. The company was founded six years ago by
Jonathan Meyer and Richard Martin to serve restaurants. It offers
reliably high-quality seafood, domestic and imported, at prices a
trifle lower than those at Dean &AMP; DeLuca nearby or at some uptown
seafood stores.
</P>
<P>
   For example, blackfish and Atlantic salmon fillets are $10.95 a
pound, and whole skate and monkfish on the bone are $4.95 a pound.
Sea scallops are $16.95 a pound, but they are the genuine Maine
diver's kind. The market has 12 varieties of oysters for New Year's
Eve, $1.10 to $1.40 each.
</P>
<P>
   The impeccable quality is up to top restaurant standards, and
the fish is iced and handled well. The service is equally fine. Pin
bones are plucked out of salmon fillets, and sea urchins ($5.95
each) are cleaned for you. The store can also provide cooking tips.
</P>
<P>
   It's good to call to see what's available, or to order. The
retail hours Monday through Friday are noon to 7 p.m.; Saturday, 10
a.m. to 6 p.m., and Sunday, noon to 5 p.m. Telephone: (212)
625-9971.
</P>
<P>
   Chocolate and Friends
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ If you think a chocolate cherry is merely a whole
cherry in white goo encased in chocolate, think again. There are
other ways to combine the two symbiotic flavors.
</P>
<P>
   Wine Designs, a wine-theme mail-order company in Ventura,
Calif., has dried cherries that have been soaked in pinot noir,
covered in magenta-tinted milk chocolate and packed in a pretty
tin. They are $16.95, plus $5.95 shipping, and can be ordered at
(888) 987-5700. Similar dried cherries enrobed in chocolate but
without the wine bath and with artificial coloring, are also sold
at Starbucks, $2.99 for 4 ounces.
</P>
<P>
   Petrossian's tin of shiny coffee-bean-size chocolate candies,
each filled with a potent little mouthful of cherry brandy, is $40
for 12 ounces at the Petrossian boutique, 182 West 58th St. They
can also be ordered for delivery, $10 extra, at (800) 828-9241.
</P>
<P>
   Cut-Rate Catering
</P>
<P>
   NEW YORK _ Karen Lee, a caterer who specializes in Chinese
cooking but who also prepares Mediterranean and fusion menus, may
not lack for customers this week, but with an eye to the future,
she is offering a discount on all parties that are given from Jan.
4 to Feb. 1.
</P>
<P>
   For events with 20 guests or fewer, the price reduction is 10
percent; it goes up to 20 percent for larger parties. Ms. Lee's
prices for a cocktail party range from $31 to $55 a person,
depending on the number of guests. For a sit-down dinner, the cost
ranges from $70 to $135 a person. Those prices do not include chefs
and waiters.
</P>
<P>
   Also on sale for a week starting Monday are selections from the
market table at Flavors, 8 West 18th St. Pamela Morgan, the owner,
is celebrating her fifth anniversary by reducing the price for
salads, grain dishes and other fare on the buffet to $5 a pound
from $7.50.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
