   If you haven't heard ...
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times Syndicate is offering to newspapers short
100-word excerpts from Harold Evans' best seller, ``The American
Century,'' which captures the great events, personalities and
movements of the past 100 years. Subscribers can use one a day in
1999, or compile them to form weekly or monthly specials _ WITH ART
AND A QUARK-BASED LAYOUT!
</P>
<P>
   To celebrate the release of these excerpts, we have been running
a history trivia quiz based on the book. Editors who faxed back the
correct answers won a copy of ``The American Century.''
</P>
<P>
   THE ANSWERS TO YESTERDAY'S QUESTIONS:
</P>
<P>
   1. AL NEUHARTH founded USA Today?
</P>
<P>
   2. The reporter who incurred President John F. Kennedy's
disfavor because of his reporting from Vietnam was DAVID
HALBERSTAM.
</P>
<P>
   Congratulations to MICHAEL LONSFORD, wine critic at The Houston
Chronicle, and HAROLD HANKA, Assistant Managing Editor at The Day.
Copies of the book ``The American Century'' are in the mail!
</P>
<P>
   FOR MORE INFORMATION ON ``THE AMERICAN CENTURY'' ... call
888-269-8796 and you'll automatically be connected to a salesperson
in your territory.
</P>
<P>
   Thank You.
</P>
