   SPORTS-DRUGS98 _ AUSTIN, Texas _ On the playing field, 1998 was
the best of years. But off the field, it was the worst of years.
For every great thrill, there was an eerie chill about what was
powering those electrifying performances. For every cheer, there
was a gnawing fear in sport's Year of Playing Dangerously. It was a
year when performance-enhancing substances stole headlines in a
wide spectrum of sports, on a range of continents. It was a year
that made 1988, the infamous one stained by Ben Johnson's Olympic
drug scandal, look almost pristine. IN TWO TAKES. (Maher, Austin
