huge wrestling fan, so when he's away from football he spends a lot
of time at wrestling events. Bill Goldberg, a former UGA player who
is the biggest name in wrestling, is among Tobeck's best friends.
(Winkeljohn, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   COLLEGES
</P>
<P>
   FBC-CHAMP-GONE _ University of Georgia coach Jim Donnan says
star player Champ Bailey will not return to the Bulldogs. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATOR-GATECH _ Judging by statistics, the Georgia Tech
defense of 1998 was nearly as bad as the one which finished last in
the ACC in '97. But the Jacket defense had a knack for making big
plays this season and it helped the team to a 9-2 record and a
berth in the Gator Bowl. The architect of the defense was
coordinator Randy Edsall, who will be leaving Tech after the game
for the head coaching position at the University of Connecticut.
What has been Edsall's impact on the Jacket defense this season and
how will the unit perform for him in his final game? (Rogers,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-GATOR-NDAME _ Feature on Notre Dame's Autry Denson, the
team's top running back and one of the key players Georgia Tech
must defend in Friday's Gator Bowl. (Levine, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-PEACH-UGA _ Matt Stinchcomb will play his final game for the
Georgia Bulldogs Thursday in the Peach Bowl, closing the door on
one of the most celebrated careers in UGA history. In addition to
his stellar performance on the field as an offensive tackle,
including several SEC and All-American honors, Stinchcomb has also
received several academic awards as well. He will likely be
selected in the first few rounds of next year's NFL draft, but he
also has a postgraduate scholarship at his disposal if the NFL
doesn't come calling. (Schlabach, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   w/FBC-PEACH-UVA _ Patrick Kerney arrived at the University of
Virginia four years ago as a walk-on interested in a career with
the school's lacrosse team. Four years later, Kerney is an
All-America defensive lineman who will likely move on to the NFL
next season. Kerney will line up against a fellow All-American,
Georgia offensive lineman Matt Stinchcomb, when the Cavaliers meet
the Bulldogs in the Peach Bowl Thursday at the Georgia Dome.
(Wilkinson, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-AUS-SUGAR _ AUSTIN, Texas _ They were a self-described
``bunch of old country boys,'' those fightin' Texas Aggies from
towns like Freer and Brownwood, Hillsboro and Kerrville, who took
New Orleans' bright lights and big-city ways by storm 59 years ago.
Prior to Friday's Sugar Bowl game with Ohio State, the last time
Texas A&AMP;M went bowling in the Big Easy was on Jan. 1, 1940. The
stakes were higher that day, albeit less publicized. The Aggies
held off hometown favorite Tulane 14-13 before a record-setting
crowd of 73,000 in Tulane's own stadium to win A&AMP;M's first and only
national football championship. In the 1990s, that's a big deal.
But on the second day of 1940, the Aggies learned of their
accomplishment while riding the train back to College Station after
a robust night in the French Quarter celebrating primarily an
undefeated (11-0) 1939 season. (Riggs, Austin American-Statesman)
</P>
<P>
   FBC-AUS-COTTON _ AUSTIN, Texas _ Something on the University of
Texas defense to advance Horns in the Cotton Bowl. (Wangrin, Austin
American-Statesman)
</P>
