<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Wednesday, Dec. 30 and thereafter. The stories will carry the
``f'' financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For
questions about stories, contact William Toren at the Daily News,
(818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   LATIMES-LAYOFFS (Los Angeles) _ The Los Angeles Times announced
its third round of layoffs in the last two months, with about 100
people, including 84 part-timers, to be laid off, primarily in
circulation. By Deborah Adamson. (Will also move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DISNEY-RULES (Los Angeles) _ With help from a transvestite
Chinese warrior, a big ape and a swarm of bugs, the Walt Disney Co.
climbed to the top of the 1998 domestic box office pile, edging
Paramount Pictures by an estimated $18 million to reign studio
supreme for the fourth time in five years. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   HOME-SALES (Los Angeles) _ Home sales across California in
November were up 11 percent over November 1997, with Los Angeles
County beating the state average in sales activity and price. By
Enrique Rivero.
</P>
<P>
   FREQUENT-FLIGHT (Los Angeles) _ With a little planning,
travelers can squeeze the most benefit from accumulated frequent
flier miles. By Dave McNary.
</P>
