<HEADLINE>
 
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has moved for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Wednesday, Dec. 30. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MCCAIN _ Sen. John McCain, R-Ariz., will take his first major step
Wednesday toward launching a presidential campaign by filing papers
to create a presidential exploratory committee. In doing so, McCain
becomes the first Republican to take such a formal step, which
allows him to begin raising the estimated $20 million he will need
next year to be considered a viable candidate in 2000. MICHAEL
MURPHY. Story has moved in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
