stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Wednesday, Dec. 30, and thereafter. If you have any questions,
please call Bob Schenet at 206-448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-QUOTA (Seattle) _ Boeing will announce Wednesday that it
has met its target quota of 550 planes delivered this year. As of
the end of the year there will be fewer than 10 undelivered planes
in storage in the deserts of California and Arizona, down from
about 30.
</P>
<P>
   By James Wallace. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   POWELLS-BOOKS (Portland, Ore.) _ Powell's, probably the largest
bookstore in the United States and maybe the world, bills itself as
the ``City of Books.'' And this Northwest institution boasts many
features of a city, being open 365 days a year, purveying food for
the stomach and the intellect, requiring a map to navigate its real
estate, having its codes and legends.
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (Story has moved in the ``l'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS (Seattle) _ _ Updating Seattle Seahawks search for
a coach to replace fired Dennis Erickson.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
</TEXT>
