Iris,'' which is being published in the United States by St.
Martin's Press, has drawn glowing reviews both as a lyric
description of the arc of a singular marriage and as an unflinching
account of the frustrations of Alzheimer's disease. (Jonathan
Player/New York Times Photo)
</P>
